The paper deals with algorithms for computing matrix products and transforming vectors, which are fundamental problems in computer science. The use of hash functions and error-correcting codes suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of FFT for polynomial multiplication suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
